\section{Epilogue}
This paper explained a systematic approach to sketch BS equation: modeling the gluon propagator, investigating the structure of the quark-gluon vertex, and constructing the quark--anti-quark scattering kernel. Using this approach, the spectrum of light-flavor mesons including ground and radial excitation states can be well described. Moreover, the approach can potentially be extended to more applications, e.g., meson form factors and baryon properties in the diquark picture.


